Operatives of the Economic Financial Crimes Commission Makurdi Zonal Command have arrested 17 internet fraud suspects known as Yahoo-Yahoo boys, in Makurdi, Benue State. A statement issued by EFCCâ€™s spokesman, Wilson Uwujaren on Monday said the suspects were arrested at different locations within Makurdi. According to him, the arrest of the suspects followed actionable intelligence on their alleged criminal activities. The suspects include, Samuel C., Uvande A., Joseph G., Ageva A., Emmanuel O., Ochiwu M., Dominic O, Ikpema S, Otse A., and Aondowase T. Others are, Audu-war L., Terver J., Dav J., Moses V., Abdullahi A., Agehson O., and Andoaver T. Uwujaren however said that the suspects would be charged to court as soon as the investigation was completed.